    "pathophysiology": "Absent or severely reduced ADAMTS13 activity (<10%) due to congenital mutation or acquired autoantibody leads to failure in cleaving ultra-large von Willebrand factor multimers. These hyperadhesive multimers accumulate on endothelial surfaces and promote spontaneous platelet adhesion and aggregation in the microvasculature. Microthrombi cause shearing of RBCs (producing schistocytes), consumption of platelets (thrombocytopenia), and end-organ ischemia (brain, heart, kidneys). The resulting microangiopathic hemolytic anemia and thrombocytopenia form the core diagnostic features.",
